comments: Barnes (TOR) establishes himself in a screening position in Dinwiddie's (WAS) path and does not deliver contact.
Avdija (WAS) places his hands on SIakam's (TOR) body during his drive to the basket, and the contact is marginal.
Avdija (WAS) places a resting hand on Siakam's (TOR) side and does not apply force as he defends Siakam's jump shot attempt.
Siakam (TOR) does not abnormally or overtly extend his leg into Avdija (WAS), and the contact is marginal.
Anunoby (TOR) and Beal (WAS) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Anunoby's (TOR) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Anunoby (TOR) places his forearm on Beal's (WAS) side as he defends Beal's drive to the basket, and the contact is marginal.
Siakam (TOR) makes marginal contact with Beal's (WAS) body after the release of his driving shot attempt.
Harrell (WAS) briefly places his hand to Anunoby's (TOR) arm underneath the basket and immediately removes his hand during the rebound.
Boucher (TOR) and Harrell (WAS) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Siakam (TOR) jumps from point A to point B when he makes contact with Harrell's (WAS) body during his upper shooting motion, which affects his shot attempt at the basket.
Anunoby (TOR) establishes himself in a screening position in Beal's (WAS) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Harrell (WAS) makes marginal body contact with Boucher (TOR) at the start of his drive, which he is able to move through.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) places his arm on VanVleet's (TOR) body during his drive to the basket and removes his hand prior to the start of VanVleet's upward shooting motion.
Barnes (TOR) jumps towards Harrell (WAS) and marginal contact occurs with Harrell's slightly extended leg defending his shot attempt.
Siakam (TOR) establishes himself in a screening position in Dinwiddie's (WAS) path and absorbs the contact.
Harrell (WAS) has a resting forearm on Siakam's (TOR) body, which he releases as both players naturally pursue the rebound.
Barnes (TOR) establishes himself in a screening position in Dinwiddie's (WAS) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Dinwiddie (WAS) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Barnes (TOR) after the release that does not affect his play at the basket.
Beal (WAS) has a resting forearm on Trent Jr.'s (TOR) side, which he extends slightly during the rebound.
Beal (WAS) lightly brushes Anunoby's (TOR) arm contesting his shot attempt at the rim, and the contact is marginal.
Avdija (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Trent Jr.'s (TOR) path and he releases away from the contact.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Anunoby's (TOR) path and does not deliver contact.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) steps out of bounds as he gathers the pass.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) makes clean contact with the ball to dislodge it from Anunoby (TOR) before incidental contact occurs.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) is the last person to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. The possession is correctly awarded to TOR.
Avdija (WAS) commits a take foul on Siakam (TOR).
